IMPORTANT :	1.Read the instructions carefully
		2.You should follow the step numbers in the respective order itself
		3.Now start your installation
                
 
	Thank you !!!!

**************************************************************************************



1. Copy ATCSDatalogger to /opt 

2. Check whether JDK 1.5 or higher version installed or not by typing "java -version" in terminal

3. If need ,set path for Java by

	editing  the /etc/environment file 

4. Configure ./ATCSDatalogger/config/DATALOGGER.xml for connecting to  ATCSServer,ATCSDatabase 

5.If need edit the /etc/hosts file for RMI Connection

		yourIP hostname
		ATCSServerIP ATCSServer_hostname 
	
	-----Eg: 192.168.2.200 user13-desktop 
		 192.168.2.230 AtcsServer
6. Confirm whether the ATCSServer is running 

6. Run ATCSDatalogger by 

	---#	sudo ./ATCSSetup.sh

